### ============================================================================
### Step 4: Composer Backend Pushes Notification
### This will trigger the webpush-go library. Since the subscription above
### is fake, devices_triggered might be 0, but status should be 200 OK.
### ============================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_ids": [
    "{{userId}}"
  ],
  "message": "Welcome to the Web Push era!",
  "title": "My SaaS Brand",
  "icon": "https://cdn-icons-png.flaticon.com/512/1006/1006771.png",
  "url": "https://git.tiagorg.pt"
}

### ============================================================================
### Step 5: Check Client's information
### ============================================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/client/info
Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}

### ============================================================================
### Step 6: Admin Regenerates API Key
### Tests key rotation.
### ============================================================================
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/clients/{{client_id}}/key
Authorization: Bearer {{masterKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

### ============================================================================
### Step 7: Admin Deletes Client
### Tests data isolation and cascading cleanup.
### ============================================================================
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/admin/clients/{{client_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{masterKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

